line_1: Pursue me with Satyr: what Harm is there in't?
line_2: There can be no Danger from what Thou shalt Print:

line_1: "Thy breath to Eliza's hath no fragrance in't;
line_2: " And thy bloom is but dull to her cheeks blushing tint.

line_1: You'll find has so much Virtue in't,
line_2: This Earth which bears his Body's Print,

line_1: While the owner ne'er knew half the good that was in't;
line_2: Here lies honest William, whose heart was a mint,
